I used it a few times on raids, for the novelty of it. This was on AoW, and I sortof thought I might be helping. But after a couple AoW kills, I stopped using it altogther.<br>
<br>
I think a month later I used it once in a lull during a raid when someone told me to &quot;Drop dead&quot; or something like that, because I thought it would be funny. I think it was.<br>
<br>
Since then, I dont use it.<br>
<br>
I suggested lots of ways I think this skill could be improved, but my current favorite is this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Make Act of Valor place a 10,000 hp Rune on the target with a one minute, or perhaps less, duration</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
<br>
This would be slighly better than a Complete Heal, which also does 10,000 hps, but practically never actually heals for that much. It has the added benefit that it ALWAYS is helpful, even if a cleric just landed a CH before you did AoV.<br>
<br>
It is important the duration is very short, because it is meant to stop immediate damage that is happening right now, not as a prebuff.<br>
<br>
Why 10,000 hit points? Well, I picked that number because that is what CH heals. With fully buffed tanks getting real close to 8k, and assuming they will get higher once everyone has gear from Vex Thall, 10k seems a nice round number that will be all of someone's hit points for at least a while to come.<br>
<br>
Would this be overpowering? I dont think so. It IS a 72 minute ability. It does cause the paladin to die. With a sufficiently short buff duration, it would only be used on someone that is taking damage right now, in order to save them long enough for an actual heal to arrive.<br>
<br>
I cant see this as making any known encounters trivial, as you would need way too many paladins with this skill to greatly change any encounter. Even if you had 10 paladins in a guild (unheard of right now), if you used them in a rotation instead of CHs, that would last less than a minute on any big mob, which doesnt seem to be significant to me on a 6-30 minute encounter. Perhaps I am wrong and someone else could design a way to exploit this ability and make an encounter easy, but I dont see it. (Please no venril sathir examples, that encounter is already trivialized by manaburn, etc, who cares if a 30+ aa point paladin might make it trivial as well).<br>
<br>
Comments?<br>
<br>
-Iustus <p><BR>
